        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/new-caledonia-accord-change-name-flag-hymn.jpg" alt="The accord could also eventually allow New Caledonians to change the territory‚Äôs name, flag and hymn" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>The accord could also eventually allow New Caledonians to change the territory‚Äôs name, flag and hymn. Credits: Sebastien Bozon / AFP</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> France and New Caledonia <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-signed-an-agreement?source=website" target="_blank">signed an agreement</a>, creating a ‚Äústate of Caledonia,‚Äù which grants more autonomy to the South Pacific territory, but falls short of full independence. The agreement introduces a Caledonian nationality, while residents will still hold French citizenship.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The background:</strong> New Caledonia has been a French territory since the 1850s. Tensions have long existed between the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-indigenous-kanak-people?source=website" target="_blank">Indigenous Kanak people</a>, who want independence, and pro-French settlers. In 2024, France proposed giving voting rights to long-term non-Kanak residents, which sparked mass protests and riots, as Kanaks feared losing political influence.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>What‚Äôs next:</strong> The agreement is meant to ease tensions and stabilize the region. The 2024 clashes caused $2.3B in damage (around 10% of New Caledonia‚Äôs GDP). The agreement includes an economic recovery plan focused on rebuilding the nickel industry, a key part of their economy.
          </p>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         A referendum on the agreement is planned for 2026.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
