          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">North Korea in Russia‚Äôs corner</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>Summary: North Korea pledges continued support for Russia, and Moscow returns the favor. </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> North Korean leader Kim Jong Un offered <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h2-3-unconditional-support-for-russia?source=website" target="_blank">unconditional support for Russia</a> in the Ukraine war, including sending 11,000 troops and laborers to help rebuild war-damaged areas. He praised Russia for addressing the "root cause" of the conflict and said its army would ultimately clinch victory.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The why:</strong> The support follows a 2024 <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-defense-pact?source=website" target="_blank">defense pact</a> between Russia and North Korea, where both sides agreed to support each other in case of external threats. It also comes after the US resumed military aid to Ukraine through NATO, which Pyongyang sees as provocative.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>The reaction:</strong> In return, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-russia-warned-the-us?source=website" target="_blank">Russia warned the US</a>, South Korea, and Japan against forming a security partnership targeting North Korea. The three countries recently held a joint air drill involving US nuclear-capable bombers near the Korean Peninsula, urging North Korea to cease nuclear development, missile testing, and <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-cyberattacks?source=website" target="_blank">cyberattacks</a> that compromise security. North Korea views these drills as invasion rehearsals and asserts it will develop nuclear weapons to defend itself.  
          </p>
        </mj-text>
