           <strong>üáÆüá∂ Iraq - PKK ends conflict.</strong> The Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) militants symbolically laid down arms in Northern Iraq, signaling a potential end to a 40-year conflict with Turkey. The PKK fighters announced their intent to continue the struggle for independence through democratic politics and judicial means. Turkish officials praised the move, but skepticism remains given past failed peace efforts (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-worldwide-10-kurdish-shift?source=website" target="_blank">Kurdish shift</a>).
