        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/bastille-day-ends-divine-right-monarchies.jpg" alt="The French Revolution, symbolized by Bastille Day, shattered the divine right of kings and the political stability of monarchies across Europe" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>The French Revolution, symbolized by Bastille Day, shattered the divine right of kings and the political stability of monarchies across Europe. Credits: Christophe Ena/AP</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> On this day in 1789, French revolutionaries seized control of the Bastille prison in Paris, an event that marked the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-foundations-h1-15-beginning-of-the-french-revolution?source=website" target="_blank">beginning of the French Revolution</a>. The Bastille was a symbol of the king‚Äôs absolute power, and though they just freed seven prisoners, the event marked the collapse of the old regime, setting the stage for major changes.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The significance:</strong> The revolution introduced the ideas of liberty, equality, and fraternity - principles that ended unfair privileges and gave ordinary people more rights. It also led to the separation of religion from politics and influenced democratic movements across the world.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The relevance:</strong> Bastille Day is a French national holiday. It‚Äôs celebrated with parades, fireworks, and concerts. This year, authorities have banned crowds from gathering on the Champs-√âlys√©es due to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-jul-25-foundations-h1-16-security-concerns?source=website" target="_blank">security concerns</a>. Still, the day remains a reminder of France‚Äôs fight for liberty and unity.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
